messages.content: nui-suite is a collection of custom nodes for ComfyUI.
Which custom node in nui-suite uses Dynamic Prompts syntax for text encoding?
The Dynamic Prompts Text Encode node in nui-suite uses Dynamic Prompts syntax for text encoding.
What is the purpose of the Feeling Lucky Text Encode node in nui-suite?
The Feeling Lucky Text Encode node in nui-suite searches for prompts on https://lexica.art based on the input. It also supports Dynamic Prompts syntax.
How does the Output String node in nui-suite function?
The Output String node in nui-suite sends a string from the backend to the frontend. It is useful for inspecting a randomly generated prompt in the frontend.
Does the Dynamic Prompts Text Encode node in nui-suite support CLIP text encoding?
Yes, the Dynamic Prompts Text Encode node in nui-suite is a CLIP text encoder that uses Dynamic Prompts syntax.
Is nui-suite an extension of ComfyUI?
Yes, nui-suite is an extension of ComfyUI, providing additional custom nodes.
Can the Feeling Lucky Text Encode node in nui-suite be used to search for prompts on websites other than https://lexica.art?
Based on the provided information, the Feeling Lucky Text Encode node in nui-suite is specifically designed to search for prompts on https://lexica.art.
